  "text": "The tissues were dehydrated through a graded ethanol series and embedded in paraffi n. The tissue blocks were transversely cut at a 5 m thickness and mounted on silane-coated glass slides (Matsunami, Osaka). The sections were treated for the intensification with 3, 3'-diaminobenzidine-4HCl (DAB, Sigma, St Louis, Mo, USA) or DAB plus cobalt chloride (CoCl2) (NyguenLegros et al., 1980 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . After the intensification, the sections were counterstained with hematoxylin or eosin, and some adjoining sections were stained with periodic acid-Schiff (PAS) or hematoxylin-eosin.",
